1
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,700
You coming or not?

2
00:03:36,566 --> 00:03:40,002
- All right, I'll get her to you right away.
- Appreciate it.

3
00:03:41,204 --> 00:03:42,228
- Hi.
- Hi.

4
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:46,704
<i>Dr. Klyczynski to ER, stat.
Dr. Klyczynski to ER, stat.</i>

5
00:03:46,943 --> 00:03:50,242
- Hi, excuse me.
- Yeah, just a minute, okay?

6
00:03:51,514 --> 00:03:54,972
- Fill this out for me and wait over there.
- No, I'm... I'm Dr. Forster.

7
00:03:55,184 --> 00:03:56,515
I was told to report here.

8
00:03:56,686 --> 00:04:00,144
You'll be covering 22 patients
on rounds today, this floor and the next.

9
00:04:00,356 --> 00:04:01,983
- Twenty-two?
- Quiet morning.

10
00:04:02,191 --> 00:04:05,058
If you get into trouble, beep me,
but don't make it a habit.

11
00:04:05,261 --> 00:04:07,752
The med students
will help you out with scutwork.

12
00:04:07,964 --> 00:04:10,694
What's he doing here?
I ordered an MRI, stat.

13
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:14,461
- Transport said about four hours.
- He could be dead in four hours.

14
00:04:14,671 --> 00:04:16,866
Never mind. Dr. Forster, MRI.

15
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:19,099
- A right, two lefts, elevator to two.
- Okay.

16
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:21,742
Follow the signs.
Hustle back here for rounds.

17
00:04:22,712 --> 00:04:24,407
Dr. Kly...

18
00:04:26,049 --> 00:04:29,507
- Are you taking me somewhere?
- I certainly hope so, sir.

19
00:04:29,719 --> 00:04:32,483
- How are you feeling today?
- Am...? Am I gonna make it?

20
00:04:33,289 --> 00:04:35,382
Yes. Absolutely.

21
00:04:39,595 --> 00:04:41,495
Alex!

22
00:04:41,698 --> 00:04:46,032
I made my famous spinach pie.
The trailer's nice and toasty.

23
00:04:46,235 --> 00:04:48,100
I can't.

24
00:04:50,606 --> 00:04:54,565
Look, it's really cold out here.
Don't get sick on me or anything.

25
00:04:54,777 --> 00:04:57,268
I never get sick.

26
00:04:58,014 --> 00:05:02,212
So I heard you bought a house,
and apparently I'm the last one to know.

27
00:05:02,418 --> 00:05:03,817
I thought I mentioned that.

28
00:05:04,053 --> 00:05:05,748
Wait.

29
00:05:06,422 --> 00:05:07,719
Where?

30
00:05:07,924 --> 00:05:10,222
Outside of town.
Up the shore a little bit.

31
00:05:10,426 --> 00:05:12,121
Up the shore? There's no houses...

32
00:05:12,328 --> 00:05:16,264
Oh, God. You don't mean that thing
with the stilts and the...?

33
00:05:18,901 --> 00:05:22,234
- You all right?
- Yeah. Are you crazy?

34
00:05:23,573 --> 00:05:26,269
Why would you take that house, Alex?

35
00:05:26,476 --> 00:05:29,138
It's made of glass. There's no privacy.

36
00:05:29,345 --> 00:05:31,006
Mona?

37
00:05:31,447 --> 00:05:33,745
Get yourself some boots.

38
00:05:36,552 --> 00:05:38,747
Hey, Gonzalez!

39
00:05:43,559 --> 00:05:45,493
- Four-thirty.
- You lost?

40
00:05:45,695 --> 00:05:48,755
- Yeah.
- Takes a while to get your bearings.

41
00:05:48,965 --> 00:05:52,093
- I'm Madhvi.
- Kate Forster. Hi.

42
00:05:52,301 --> 00:05:55,702
Oh, wrong floor.
Where'd you do your residency?

43
00:05:55,938 --> 00:05:58,702
Just a little community hospital
up on the North Shore.

44
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:22,898
<i>Dear new tenant,
welcome to your new home.</i>

45
00:06:23,132 --> 00:06:24,861
<i>As the previous tenant, let me say...</i>

46
00:06:25,101 --> 00:06:28,036
<i>...I hope you'll like living here
as much as I did.</i>

47
00:06:28,237 --> 00:06:31,331
<i>I filed the change of address
with the post office...</i>

48
00:06:31,541 --> 00:06:33,873
<i>...but you know
what a crapshoot that can be.</i>

49
00:06:34,110 --> 00:06:37,739
<i>So if anything slips through, would you
do me a favor and forward my mail?</i>

50
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:41,643
<i>I'd appreciate it.
My new address is below.</i>

51
00:06:41,851 --> 00:06:45,685
<i>Thanks in advance. P. S:</i>

52
00:06:45,888 --> 00:06:50,382
"Sorry about the paw prints by the front
door. They were there when I moved in.

53
00:06:50,860 --> 00:06:53,886
Same with the box in the attic. "

54
00:06:55,731 --> 00:06:59,997
Paw prints?
What the hell is she talking about?

55
00:07:14,083 --> 00:07:17,519
Hey, baby girl. Hi. Hi. Hey.

56
00:07:28,664 --> 00:07:30,757
Fix the light.

57
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:33,894
Get dog food, huh?

58
00:07:34,937 --> 00:07:36,871
Get human food.

59
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:08,431
Hey. Hey.

60
00:08:13,309 --> 00:08:15,470
Hey, come here.

61
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:28,614
Sixty degrees on Valentine's Day.
Can't be Chicago.

62
00:08:28,824 --> 00:08:31,190
The TV says it's global warming.

63
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:35,160
The icebergs start melting,
water covers the Earth.

64
00:08:35,364 --> 00:08:38,026
Thank God we won't live to see it.

65
00:08:39,435 --> 00:08:40,868
What's this?

66
00:08:41,671 --> 00:08:43,639
That's nothing.
It's one of your father's.

67
00:08:43,839 --> 00:08:47,275
- Dostoyevsky?
- Oh, yeah.

68
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:53,947
It's about a guy who breaks the neck
of a poor woman with an axe...

69
00:08:54,150 --> 00:08:57,950
..and, so far, keeps wandering
around regretting it.

70
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:02,757
This is good.

71
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:06,360
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah. It's really good.

72
00:09:07,563 --> 00:09:08,552
I'll meet you there.

73
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:10,163
What are you thinking?

74
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,065
My folks are coming into town.

75
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:13,962
Nothing.

76
00:09:14,170 --> 00:09:18,402
When your father passed away,
it was hard. It still is hard.

77
00:09:18,574 --> 00:09:23,511
Holding his books,
I feel like he's with me somehow.

78
00:09:23,713 --> 00:09:26,477
Knowing that he was once
on the same pages...

79
00:09:26,682 --> 00:09:28,843
..reading the same words.

80
00:09:34,090 --> 00:09:37,685
Oh, my God!
Somebody call an ambulance!

81
00:09:38,394 --> 00:09:40,055
We need an ambulance at Daley Plaza.

82
00:09:40,296 --> 00:09:43,231
A man has been struck by a bus.
Get an EMT crew here. Sir...

83
00:09:43,432 --> 00:09:45,297
Get out the street.
Get on the sidewalk.

84
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:47,298
- On the sidewalk. Off the street.
- Sir?

85
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:50,028
Get on the sidewalk!
Get on the sidewalk!

86
00:09:50,206 --> 00:09:53,505
I'd like to get the foundation
on number 17 dug today.

87
00:09:54,110 --> 00:09:56,874
Look, I know you're
kind of new around here, kid.

88
00:09:57,079 --> 00:09:58,706
What?

89
00:09:58,914 --> 00:10:02,042
I can't get to 17 until
at least next week.

90
00:10:02,251 --> 00:10:05,243
Come on, Mulhern.
That's bullshit and you know it.

91
00:10:05,454 --> 00:10:07,752
Take Clemens and Rodriguez
off of roofing.

92
00:10:07,957 --> 00:10:10,619
Jorge can run the backhoe
they're not using on 14...

93
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:13,021
..and grab four or five
of those other guys...

94
00:10:13,229 --> 00:10:15,527
..who are doing nothing
on seven and 10.

95
00:10:15,731 --> 00:10:19,326
Paulie, Carlos, Frank, Danny,
and what's-his-name, the tall guy?

96
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:22,026
- Rafael.
- Rafael.

97
00:10:22,238 --> 00:10:25,036
- Let's go.
- Okay.

98
00:10:25,241 --> 00:10:26,765
- Ready?
- Yeah.

99
00:10:26,976 --> 00:10:29,308
- Well, I need it to 10 and 11.
- Hey!

100
00:10:32,915 --> 00:10:35,782
<i>Housekeeping ER
to the Suture Room, please.</i>

101
00:10:35,985 --> 00:10:39,477
<i>Housekeeping ER to the Suture Room.</i>

102
00:10:42,425 --> 00:10:45,087
- Hey.
- Hi.

103
00:10:45,294 --> 00:10:48,127
I heard about Daley Plaza.

104
00:10:48,998 --> 00:10:51,660
EMT said you fought hard for the guy.

105
00:10:52,134 --> 00:10:55,069
Yeah. Really knocked myself out.

106
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:59,799
<i>Kate, I'm going to tell you
what I tell every young doctor.</i>

107
00:11:00,009 --> 00:11:03,001
<i>Hopefully, you'll be the first to listen.</i>

108
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:08,911
<i>On your day off, get as far away
from this place as you can.</i>

109
00:11:09,118 --> 00:11:14,420
<i>Go someplace where you feel
most like yourself.</i>

110
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:11,438
<i>Dear Ms. Forster:</i>

111
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:12,978
<i>I got your note...</i>

112
00:12:13,182 --> 00:12:16,447
<i>...and I'm afraid there must be
some kind of misunderstanding.</i>

113
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:20,588
<i>As far as I know, the lake house
has been empty for several years.</i>

114
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:24,350
<i>Maybe your note was intended for
the Sandburg house down the shore...</i>

115
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:28,052
"... since no one has lived
in this house for years.

116
00:12:29,064 --> 00:12:32,192
But I'm curious about the paw prints. "

117
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:41,168
<i>Dear Mr. Wyler, I'm very familiar
with the Sandburg cottage...</i>

118
00:12:41,377 --> 00:12:43,902
<i>...and I can guarantee
I never lived there.</i>

119
00:12:44,113 --> 00:12:47,879
<i>I'm old-fashioned, but I don't think a
cottage should be over 6000 square feet.</i>

120
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:50,051
<i>So let me try again.</i>

121
00:12:50,252 --> 00:12:53,415
<i>I used to live at the lake house,
then I moved.</i>

122
00:12:53,622 --> 00:12:57,251
<i>Now I live at 1620 North Racine
in Chicago.</i>

123
00:12:57,493 --> 00:13:00,519
<i>I'd appreciate it if you would
forward my mail if you get any.</i>

124
00:13:00,729 --> 00:13:04,495
<i>Oh, by the way, it's 2006.</i>

125
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:07,294
<i>Has been all year, ask anyone.</i>

126
00:13:07,536 --> 00:13:10,004
2006?

127
00:13:10,573 --> 00:13:12,905
What does she mean, 2006?

128
00:13:13,576 --> 00:13:15,544
God.

129
00:13:15,811 --> 00:13:16,800
Oh, God.

130
00:13:19,949 --> 00:13:22,110
- Good morning, Mr. Wyler.
- Morning, Mr. Wyler.

131
00:13:22,318 --> 00:13:23,808
- Morning, sir.
- Morning, morning.

132
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:25,816
Hello, Mr. Wyler.

133
00:13:26,322 --> 00:13:28,290
Mr. Wyler.

134
00:13:29,091 --> 00:13:30,956
Sir.

135
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:36,392
Well, obviously,
I derived my inspiration...

136
00:13:36,599 --> 00:13:39,830
..for the metaphor
of the fugue, the loop...

137
00:13:41,670 --> 00:13:43,331
Yeah.

138
00:14:03,158 --> 00:14:06,457
- Two hours of that shit. You kidding me?
- What are you talking about?

139
00:14:06,662 --> 00:14:11,190
- He didn't say a word.
- Sadistic, bitter, bitter old man.

140
00:14:11,433 --> 00:14:14,368
I think you're being
a little overdramatic.

141
00:14:18,207 --> 00:14:20,004
Where are you going?

142
00:14:28,817 --> 00:14:31,149
Man, I love that place.

143
00:14:52,508 --> 00:14:55,341
I can't believe that thing's
still running.

144
00:14:58,347 --> 00:14:59,974
Yep.

145
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:02,716
You look like shit.

146
00:15:03,552 --> 00:15:05,349
I missed you too.

147
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:26,403
Hey, forget about him.

148
00:15:30,879 --> 00:15:32,904
- Condos.
- Riviera Estates.

149
00:15:33,148 --> 00:15:34,911
- You're joking.
- I don't believe this.

150
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:36,947
I come back after four years...

151
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:39,051
..and I get this in front of me.
- What?

152
00:15:39,254 --> 00:15:41,381
My brother thinking
he's Frank Lloyd Whatever.

153
00:15:41,590 --> 00:15:43,558
- Oh, come on.
- Dad keeps you hostage...

154
00:15:43,759 --> 00:15:46,455
..in that little
mythmaking factory of his...

155
00:15:46,695 --> 00:15:50,028
..while you haven't built so much as
a phone booth or a hamster cage.

156
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:51,894
That's funny you say that, actually.

157
00:15:52,101 --> 00:15:55,161
I have a hamster cage in mind.
A development of them, actually.

158
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:58,534
Prefab, no foundations.
What do you think about that?

159
00:15:58,741 --> 00:16:01,938
See, that's what I'm talking about.
You have vision.

160
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:04,808
Speaking of which...

161
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:08,312
..I'd like you to know
I bought a house.

162
00:16:08,484 --> 00:16:10,543
- Where?
- On the lake.

163
00:16:10,953 --> 00:16:12,921
A lake house.
So you are making some money.

164
00:16:13,088 --> 00:16:15,579
Well, it's a dump.
Been abandoned for years, but...

165
00:16:15,791 --> 00:16:18,055
So you got an abandoned,
haunted lake hou...

166
00:16:18,260 --> 00:16:19,818
That's as good a reason as any...

167
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:22,826
..for selling out and joining
the flabby-developers' guild.

168
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:26,432
- How about this? I even got a dog.
- You got a dog?

169
00:16:27,636 --> 00:16:32,403
He just showed up at the house
from out of nowhere.

170
00:16:44,453 --> 00:16:47,149
- What are we doing here?
- I have to deliver a letter.

171
00:16:47,356 --> 00:16:51,793
It should be here.
1620 North Racine.

172
00:16:55,130 --> 00:16:56,791
But...

173
00:16:58,133 --> 00:16:59,361
..there's nothing here.

174
00:17:01,537 --> 00:17:04,768
Are we meeting someone?
Does somebody live here? What?

175
00:17:05,174 --> 00:17:06,869
Yeah.

176
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:09,304
I thought so.

177
00:17:09,712 --> 00:17:10,940
Should we ring the bell?

178
00:17:29,898 --> 00:17:31,559
<i>Dear Ms. Forster:</i>

179
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:35,497
<i>I went to 1620 North Racine,
and it's not there.</i>

180
00:17:35,904 --> 00:17:37,895
<i>It's just a construction site.</i>

181
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:42,201
<i>From the pictures it looks nice,
but not for another 18 months.</i>

182
00:17:42,411 --> 00:17:44,379
<i>What am I missing here?</i>

183
00:17:44,580 --> 00:17:48,072
<i>Maybe you got the address wrong,
because you got the date wrong too.</i>

184
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:51,150
You really wanna play this game.

185
00:17:51,987 --> 00:17:57,289
If you are truly in the year 2004...

186
00:17:57,993 --> 00:18:00,291
..then...

187
00:18:02,564 --> 00:18:04,657
..be forewarned.

188
00:18:06,401 --> 00:18:10,929
Remember that day?
You were not happy. Remember that?

189
00:18:12,107 --> 00:18:13,335
I know.

190
00:18:13,942 --> 00:18:16,877
<i>Okay, my mystery correspondent,
I get it.</i>

191
00:18:17,079 --> 00:18:20,446
<i>Just in case you really are
where and when you think you are...</i>

192
00:18:20,682 --> 00:18:22,240
<i>...you'll need this.</i>

193
00:18:22,451 --> 00:18:25,750
<i>There was a freak late snow that spring
and everyone got sick.</i>

194
00:18:25,954 --> 00:18:30,584
<i>So plenty of rest, lots of fluids.
Doctor's orders.</i>

195
00:18:30,826 --> 00:18:33,693
Snow. Right.

196
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:41,336
Yeah, come to papa.

197
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:19,362
Jackie.

198
00:20:20,535 --> 00:20:22,298
Jack.

199
00:20:22,704 --> 00:20:25,832
Jack, come on. Come on, girl.
Come on, come on. Jack.

200
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:15,248
"Lmpossible, I know. Not possible...

201
00:21:15,691 --> 00:21:17,682
..but it's happening. "

202
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:29,867
Okay.

203
00:21:34,109 --> 00:21:35,804
Where am I?

204
00:21:40,615 --> 00:21:42,742
Very clever.

205
00:21:44,753 --> 00:21:46,778
"The lake house. "

206
00:21:47,222 --> 00:21:50,214
The lake house. As you can see,
I, too, am at the lake house...

207
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:53,555
..but I'm getting tired of these games
so I'm leaving, okay? Bye.

208
00:21:53,729 --> 00:21:54,957
Thank you. Bye.

209
00:21:57,532 --> 00:22:00,729
Maybe we should
introduce ourselves properly.

210
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:09,275
<i>I'm a doctor,
dedicated to curing the sick.</i>

211
00:22:09,644 --> 00:22:11,339
<i>At least, trying to.</i>

212
00:22:12,481 --> 00:22:14,813
<i>I'm an architect. I like to build.</i>

213
00:22:15,050 --> 00:22:17,848
<i>And while I wouldn't say
my current project is ideal...</i>

214
00:22:18,086 --> 00:22:23,149
<i>...it allows me to be here, in this place,
and that's enough for now.</i>

215
00:22:23,492 --> 00:22:27,451
<i>But tell me something. If you're working
in a hospital in Chicago now...</i>

216
00:22:27,662 --> 00:22:30,597
<i>...where were you before, in my time?</i>

217
00:22:31,366 --> 00:22:32,993
<i>Two years ago, in your time...</i>

218
00:22:33,201 --> 00:22:37,297
<i>...I was working
in internal medicine in Madison.</i>

219
00:22:40,342 --> 00:22:41,639
<i>Tell me about the future.</i>

220
00:22:42,644 --> 00:22:45,374
<i>What's it like in the year 2006?</i>

221
00:22:46,715 --> 00:22:49,445
<i>I'm afraid the world's
pretty much the same.</i>

222
00:22:50,652 --> 00:22:54,645
<i>Of course, we all dress in shiny metal
jump suits and drive flying cars...</i>

223
00:22:54,856 --> 00:22:58,587
<i>...and no one talks anymore
because we can read each other's minds.</i>

224
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:01,888
<i>But the truth is, man from the past...</i>

225
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:05,657
<i>...not much has really changed
in 2006.</i>

226
00:23:07,469 --> 00:23:11,166
<i>Speaking of the past, though,
I've been thinking about the paw prints.</i>

227
00:23:11,373 --> 00:23:15,571
<i>- How is that possible?
- Well, I think we have the same dog.</i>

228
00:23:16,344 --> 00:23:18,869
<i>Oh, yeah? What's yours like?</i>

229
00:23:19,114 --> 00:23:22,880
<i>According to the vet,
mine is eight years old in my time...</i>

230
00:23:23,118 --> 00:23:25,109
<i>...six in yours.</i>

231
00:23:25,620 --> 00:23:31,115
<i>She's skinny, has sad eyes, snores,
and sleeps like a person.</i>

232
00:23:31,326 --> 00:23:33,624
<i>I don't know why, but I call her Jack.</i>

233
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:35,820
Hello, Jack.

234
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,560
<i>It's nice out here.</i>

235
00:23:41,837 --> 00:23:45,068
<i>Let's not go out for dinner.
Let's stay here.</i>

236
00:23:45,273 --> 00:23:47,207
<i>- Hey.
- We have to eat.</i>

237
00:23:47,409 --> 00:23:50,003
What are you doing?
You're supposed to be asleep.

238
00:23:50,378 --> 00:23:51,572
<i>I'll cook.</i>

239
00:23:52,514 --> 00:23:54,641
<i>I thought you didn't like to cook.</i>

240
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:57,545
<i>No, I don't like to cook.</i>

241
00:23:57,752 --> 00:23:59,777
Is she gonna marry him?

242
00:23:59,955 --> 00:24:03,584
- What do you think?
- I don't know. He's kind of old.

243
00:24:03,758 --> 00:24:06,955
<i>- Where are you going?
- Okay, he's not that old.</i>

244
00:24:07,529 --> 00:24:09,360
My mom's last boyfriend was bald.

245
00:24:10,065 --> 00:24:11,464
He was nice...

246
00:24:11,633 --> 00:24:14,431
..but my mom didn't marry him.
- No?

247
00:24:14,669 --> 00:24:17,536
"There's always something better
coming around the corner. "

248
00:24:17,739 --> 00:24:20,105
That's what she says.

249
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:24,103
Maybe that's what that lady should do.
Wait for something better...

250
00:24:24,312 --> 00:24:27,281
..to come around the corner.
- Maybe.

251
00:24:29,284 --> 00:24:33,050
But if she's not careful,
she could spend her whole life waiting.

252
00:24:33,989 --> 00:24:36,321
<i>Do you want me to bring
anything back with me?</i>

253
00:24:36,491 --> 00:24:39,119
<i>Yes. What about
a nice bottle of wine...</i>

254
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:41,453
<i>...to celebrate?</i>

255
00:24:41,696 --> 00:24:44,722
<i>- What time shall I come back?
- Seven o'clock.</i>

256
00:24:44,933 --> 00:24:47,697
<i>Sorry I haven't made it
to the mailbox lately.</i>

257
00:24:47,903 --> 00:24:51,839
<i>It's been a long week. All night shifts.</i>

258
00:24:52,107 --> 00:24:55,201
<i>Good to hear from you.
I thought you left me.</i>

259
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:59,141
<i>You should know that you're
my only connection to the future.</i>

260
00:24:59,781 --> 00:25:03,012
<i>How come we never talk
about the things we like?</i>

261
00:25:03,351 --> 00:25:06,843
<i>Well, let's see.
Reading the classics to Jack.</i>

262
00:25:07,088 --> 00:25:10,216
<i>- Who's his favorite?
- Dostoyevsky.</i>

263
00:25:10,425 --> 00:25:14,088
<i>For me, this city,
on a day when the light is so clear...</i>

264
00:25:14,296 --> 00:25:15,923
<i>...that I can touch every detail...</i>

265
00:25:16,131 --> 00:25:18,793
<i>...every brick and window
in the buildings I love.</i>

266
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:23,596
<i>Come on, take a walk with me
this Saturday. Let me show you.</i>

267
00:25:23,805 --> 00:25:27,241
<i>You're crazy. Why are you going
through all this trouble for me?</i>

268
00:25:27,442 --> 00:25:30,468
<i>No trouble. Summer's here.</i>

269
00:25:43,124 --> 00:25:46,787
<i>Okay, your turn. Favorite things.</i>

270
00:25:46,995 --> 00:25:49,828
<i>Where to start? Okay.</i>

271
00:25:50,031 --> 00:25:53,125
<i>When I smell the flowers
before I see them.</i>

272
00:25:53,335 --> 00:25:57,635
<i>When it starts to rain
just as the picnic is ending.</i>

273
00:25:57,839 --> 00:26:01,707
<i>And I love the smell of Jack's paws.</i>

274
00:26:01,910 --> 00:26:04,538
<i>You didn't forget
to mention your husband, did you?</i>

275
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:09,007
<i>Well, of course I love my husband,
who is also a doctor.</i>

276
00:26:09,217 --> 00:26:11,651
<i>Plastic surgeon
for small farm animals.</i>

277
00:26:11,853 --> 00:26:14,151
<i>Good. I'm married too.</i>

278
00:26:14,356 --> 00:26:17,814
<i>I've got eight children,
and none of them look like me.</i>

279
00:26:18,026 --> 00:26:21,189
<i>- I'm worried, Kate.
- I would be too.</i>

280
00:26:21,596 --> 00:26:22,995
<i>I'm single.</i>

281
00:26:23,832 --> 00:26:25,595
<i>Me too.</i>

282
00:26:28,670 --> 00:26:30,501
<i>Number 27.</i>

283
00:26:30,705 --> 00:26:32,866
<i>She's a beauty.
My father used to tell me...</i>

284
00:26:33,074 --> 00:26:35,941
<i>...she was the grandma
for all the houses in the city.</i>

285
00:26:36,177 --> 00:26:39,613
<i>He used to take me on walks
like I'm taking you now.</i>

286
00:26:40,048 --> 00:26:43,313
<i>- Alex?
- Kate?</i>

287
00:26:43,518 --> 00:26:46,351
<i>I wish we could have
done this walk together.</i>

288
00:27:01,436 --> 00:27:03,233
So, what do you think?

289
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:05,972
He sounds like a nice boy.

290
00:27:06,141 --> 00:27:08,837
Sounds like a nice boy.
Anything else?

291
00:27:09,044 --> 00:27:12,377
- He has wonderful penmanship.
- Mother...

292
00:27:12,547 --> 00:27:14,947
..look at the date on the letter.
The date.

293
00:27:15,150 --> 00:27:16,640
- You mean the time thing?
- Yes.

294
00:27:16,885 --> 00:27:19,479
- That's just a detail.
- Just a detail?

295
00:27:28,563 --> 00:27:31,657
About the...
The other day...

296
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:36,769
..it was not a good moment.
I was in a hell of a hurry.

297
00:27:37,105 --> 00:27:38,732
Of course.

298
00:27:40,141 --> 00:27:42,302
You've got some nice pieces here.

299
00:27:42,510 --> 00:27:46,310
Oh, yeah. Music's fine, music helps.

300
00:27:47,015 --> 00:27:48,676
It's like Nietzsche says:

301
00:27:48,917 --> 00:27:52,182
- "Life would be senseless... "
- "Without music. "

302
00:27:53,088 --> 00:27:54,988
I guess I told you that, huh?

303
00:27:55,190 --> 00:27:56,623
Pour yourself a drink.

304
00:27:56,825 --> 00:28:00,090
Can you appreciate
a good wine by now?

305
00:28:00,295 --> 00:28:02,195
You bet.

306
00:28:03,031 --> 00:28:06,125
You know, you'll have to forgive
your father for being curious...

307
00:28:06,334 --> 00:28:09,497
..but where have you been
all these years?

308
00:28:09,838 --> 00:28:13,103
I thought your Kerouac days
were behind you.

309
00:28:14,109 --> 00:28:16,907
- I'm sorry, what?
- What?

310
00:28:18,146 --> 00:28:20,637
Oh, you can come up, if you like.

311
00:28:29,357 --> 00:28:30,984
What are you working on?

312
00:28:31,159 --> 00:28:34,219
Oh, I'm just...
I'm just remembering things.

313
00:28:34,462 --> 00:28:37,124
It's not such an easy job,
let me tell you.

314
00:28:37,332 --> 00:28:40,301
Nor is it particularly innocent,
in my case.

315
00:28:40,502 --> 00:28:43,869
Your father is writing his memoirs.

316
00:28:45,573 --> 00:28:47,234
- Are we in it?
- What do you think?

317
00:28:47,409 --> 00:28:49,172
Do you wanna be?

318
00:28:50,311 --> 00:28:51,710
Do you?

319
00:28:51,946 --> 00:28:55,541
Of course.
You were all a part of your father's life.

320
00:28:56,818 --> 00:28:58,911
Why are you talking to me
in the third person?

321
00:28:59,087 --> 00:29:00,748
Well, I... I don't...

322
00:29:00,989 --> 00:29:04,322
Because I'm writing about myself,
I suppose. Why, doesn't it suit you?

323
00:29:07,195 --> 00:29:10,687
I thought you might like these.

324
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:14,898
What are these?
Something you've been working on?

325
00:29:15,103 --> 00:29:17,970
No, they're... They're yours.

326
00:29:18,173 --> 00:29:22,234
From a house I just bought
on the lake.

327
00:29:23,278 --> 00:29:27,009
Oh, yes, I heard. They said
some sleazy little condo developer...

328
00:29:27,215 --> 00:29:29,206
..had snapped it up.

329
00:29:29,584 --> 00:29:32,849
Oh, come on. Indulge your father.

330
00:29:33,054 --> 00:29:36,046
Can't you take a little joke,
for God's sake?

331
00:29:36,391 --> 00:29:38,188
Come on.

332
00:29:38,359 --> 00:29:40,088
Tell me.

333
00:29:40,562 --> 00:29:42,757
Where have you been?
I really want to know.

334
00:29:42,997 --> 00:29:45,488
I was trying to forget you.

335
00:29:47,235 --> 00:29:49,567
Or forgive you.

336
00:29:50,905 --> 00:29:53,066
Did you succeed?

337
00:29:55,376 --> 00:29:57,071
No.

338
00:30:01,416 --> 00:30:04,442
Let me know
if you need any help remembering.

339
00:30:06,454 --> 00:30:09,514
Oh, yeah, I will.

340
00:30:10,291 --> 00:30:13,920
Charging 360. Get 1 milligram of epi.
Have 300 amio ready in case we need it.

341
00:30:14,128 --> 00:30:16,756
- All clear?
- Clear.

342
00:30:18,933 --> 00:30:21,026
Hold compression, start bagging.

343
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:22,533
He's got a rhythm. Slow.

344
00:30:22,737 --> 00:30:25,331
- Do we have a pulse with that?
- We got a pulse, thready.

345
00:30:25,573 --> 00:30:27,473
<i>- It's getting stronger.
- Long days, these days.</i>

346
00:30:27,675 --> 00:30:30,405
<i>I just worked 30 hours straight.</i>

347
00:30:30,612 --> 00:30:33,103
<i>Every time I stop to take a breath...</i>

348
00:30:33,314 --> 00:30:36,579
<i>...I realize how isolated
I've let myself become.</i>

349
00:30:36,751 --> 00:30:41,688
<i>Believe me,
you can get a bit desperate.</i>

350
00:30:43,324 --> 00:30:45,792
That one? Okay. There you go.

351
00:30:45,994 --> 00:30:50,192
Nice move. Very nice. Nice.

352
00:30:52,834 --> 00:30:55,860
<i>It's not that I'm complaining,
I love my work.</i>

353
00:30:56,104 --> 00:31:00,438
<i>And our tour through Chicago
opened my eyes to its beauty.</i>

354
00:31:00,642 --> 00:31:03,577
<i>But my heart still misses
the lake house...</i>

355
00:31:03,778 --> 00:31:05,973
<i>...and its trees.</i>

356
00:31:06,881 --> 00:31:09,509
<i>I miss those trees so much.</i>

357
00:32:26,761 --> 00:32:30,288
<i>Don't worry, Kate.
We'll be together in time.</i>

358
00:32:30,531 --> 00:32:33,864
<i>Even if we're far apart,
I'll find a way to be close to you...</i>

359
00:32:34,068 --> 00:32:36,093
<i>...and take care of you.</i>

360
00:32:41,476 --> 00:32:43,273
Katerina.

361
00:32:44,712 --> 00:32:46,475
Take this.

362
00:32:46,948 --> 00:32:49,815
- You should eat more. You too skinny.
- I'm not too skinny.

363
00:32:49,984 --> 00:32:53,249
Remember how you used to eat
when you were little?

364
00:32:53,454 --> 00:32:55,183
- With your hands.
- Yes, I remember.

365
00:32:55,390 --> 00:32:58,223
Now, did you or did you not
write to each other?

366
00:32:58,593 --> 00:33:00,493
- To your father?
- No, to Clark Gable.

367
00:33:00,728 --> 00:33:03,322
Yes, to Dad.

368
00:33:05,767 --> 00:33:07,496
I...

369
00:33:09,937 --> 00:33:11,461
What, Mom?

370
00:33:11,706 --> 00:33:13,697
Before your father...

371
00:33:13,908 --> 00:33:15,637
Yeah?

372
00:33:16,511 --> 00:33:20,709
There was this boy.

373
00:33:22,650 --> 00:33:24,117
Did you love him?

374
00:33:24,952 --> 00:33:26,681
Yeah.

375
00:33:32,026 --> 00:33:34,620
Well, why didn't you marry him?

376
00:33:35,997 --> 00:33:39,831
So that you could ask me
this question someday.

377
00:33:49,977 --> 00:33:52,036
Looks smaller.

378
00:33:54,015 --> 00:33:56,245
When did he complete it?

379
00:33:57,285 --> 00:33:59,845
You weren't born yet,
and I was 8.

380
00:34:04,559 --> 00:34:07,619
Corbusier meets Frank Lloyd Wright.

381
00:34:08,329 --> 00:34:11,321
You know, Dad played cards
with both of them.

382
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:15,858
- Sharing a joint.
- Yeah, well...

383
00:34:16,471 --> 00:34:18,405
Can't swim.

384
00:34:18,773 --> 00:34:22,470
There should be a stairway
down to the water, a porch, a deck.

385
00:34:23,044 --> 00:34:25,512
Here, you're in a...
In a box.

386
00:34:25,713 --> 00:34:28,978
A glass box with a view
to everything that's around you...

387
00:34:29,183 --> 00:34:30,650
..but you can't touch it.

388
00:34:30,852 --> 00:34:35,186
No interconnection
between you and what you're looking at.

389
00:34:35,389 --> 00:34:38,222
I don't know, you know.
He's got this big maple growing...

390
00:34:38,426 --> 00:34:41,418
..right in the middle of the house.
- Containment.

391
00:34:44,832 --> 00:34:48,495
Containment and control.

392
00:34:50,304 --> 00:34:54,331
This house is about ownership,
not connection.

393
00:34:54,942 --> 00:34:58,742
I mean, it's beautiful. Seductive, even.

394
00:34:58,946 --> 00:35:01,915
But it's incomplete.

395
00:35:04,218 --> 00:35:06,049
It was all about him.

396
00:35:07,722 --> 00:35:10,122
Dad knew how to build a house,
not a home.

397
00:35:11,125 --> 00:35:12,456
But you know...

398
00:35:13,194 --> 00:35:15,628
..I think he wants us to do
what he couldn't.

399
00:35:16,330 --> 00:35:18,423
But admitting that...

400
00:35:19,133 --> 00:35:23,194
..would mean admitting
that he came up short in some way...

401
00:35:23,404 --> 00:35:25,269
..that he could do more.

402
00:35:25,473 --> 00:35:27,532
And that tortures him.

403
00:35:28,876 --> 00:35:31,367
Do you remember
being here with Mom?

404
00:35:38,219 --> 00:35:40,278
I remember she tried
to make it work here...

405
00:35:41,556 --> 00:35:43,421
..with us...

406
00:35:44,058 --> 00:35:45,650
..with him.

407
00:35:47,795 --> 00:35:49,456
Hey, what about Visionary Vanguard?

408
00:35:49,630 --> 00:35:52,258
- What about it?
- Come on.

409
00:35:52,433 --> 00:35:56,301
You can't convince me you're gonna
be happy building saltboxes for tourists.

410
00:35:56,804 --> 00:35:59,068
Nobody's gonna admire you for that.

411
00:35:59,273 --> 00:36:02,333
- Admire me for that?
- Yeah, Visionary Vanguard.

412
00:36:03,110 --> 00:36:05,101
That's your idea.

413
00:36:05,313 --> 00:36:07,144
I can't. But you can keep the name.

414
00:36:07,315 --> 00:36:09,476
No, come on.
It's gotta be you and me.

415
00:36:09,684 --> 00:36:12,448
Henry, I'm sorry, I can't.

416
00:36:12,653 --> 00:36:14,143
I just...

417
00:36:14,388 --> 00:36:17,585
- What?
- I've got other plans.

418
00:36:17,758 --> 00:36:19,783
You have a girlfriend?

419
00:36:21,629 --> 00:36:22,687
No...

420
00:36:22,864 --> 00:36:24,627
No.

421
00:36:24,999 --> 00:36:28,127
- What is that? You hesitated.
- No, I didn't hesitate.

422
00:36:29,937 --> 00:36:32,337
Come on, man.
I don't have any time for that.

423
00:36:33,841 --> 00:36:35,900
What does time have to do with it?

424
00:36:36,677 --> 00:36:39,043
Oh, you're gonna think I'm crazy.

425
00:36:43,985 --> 00:36:46,419
<i>My dearest Mr. Wyler:</i>

426
00:36:46,621 --> 00:36:49,351
<i>Are you willing to play a game
with me?</i>

427
00:36:49,991 --> 00:36:53,222
<i>Two years ago today,
I was taking the 145 train to Madison...</i>

428
00:36:53,461 --> 00:36:56,828
<i>...from the Riverside station
and I forgot something there.</i>

429
00:36:57,031 --> 00:36:59,556
<i>It was a gift from my father.</i>

430
00:37:00,034 --> 00:37:04,027
<i>If you find it,
can you please put it in the mailbox?</i>

431
00:37:05,039 --> 00:37:07,166
<i>It would mean a lot.</i>

432
00:37:07,475 --> 00:37:10,706
<i>Yours, Kate.</i>

433
00:37:26,460 --> 00:37:31,454
- Final call for the 5:46 to Madison.
- Do you really wanna know? Come on.

434
00:37:31,666 --> 00:37:33,861
- All aboard.
- Okay.

435
00:37:43,978 --> 00:37:45,570
I'll call you.

436
00:38:26,887 --> 00:38:30,254
<i>Kate, I found it. I have it with me.</i>

437
00:38:30,458 --> 00:38:33,154
<i>One day I'll get it to you. Trust me.</i>

438
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:36,386
<i>I know how important it is to you.</i>

439
00:38:37,665 --> 00:38:41,101
<i>You might not remember,
but we saw each other.</i>

440
00:38:41,302 --> 00:38:43,395
<i>At least, I saw you.</i>

441
00:38:44,638 --> 00:38:48,802
<i>You never told me
how beautiful you are.</i>

442
00:38:49,043 --> 00:38:51,534
<i>Well, maybe you saw somebody else.</i>

443
00:38:51,746 --> 00:38:54,237
<i>That was a bad hair year for me.</i>

444
00:38:54,448 --> 00:38:57,781
<i>Long brown hair.
Gentle, unguarded eyes.</i>

445
00:38:57,985 --> 00:38:59,850
<i>Okay, okay, okay.</i>

446
00:39:00,087 --> 00:39:01,918
<i>You saw me.</i>

447
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:04,751
<i>But I still don't know
what you look like.</i>

448
00:39:06,327 --> 00:39:09,785
<i>Well, why don't we just get together
in the future...</i>

449
00:39:09,997 --> 00:39:12,659
<i>...and you can let me know
what you think.</i>

450
00:39:13,634 --> 00:39:15,431
It's a date.

451
00:39:18,639 --> 00:39:20,129
Okay.

452
00:39:20,341 --> 00:39:24,675
Why don't you call me
July 10th, 2006...

453
00:39:24,879 --> 00:39:30,112
..at 9:05 p. m.

454
00:39:44,799 --> 00:39:47,165
<i>- Hello.
- Kate?</i>

455
00:39:47,368 --> 00:39:50,201
<i>- Yes.
- It's Morgan.</i>

456
00:39:53,107 --> 00:39:54,699
Morgan.

457
00:39:54,909 --> 00:39:57,810
<i>I'm in Chicago. I came for a meeting,
but it was canceled...</i>

458
00:39:58,012 --> 00:39:59,741
<i>...so I thought I'd give you a call.</i>

459
00:40:00,548 --> 00:40:02,675
Hey, have you eaten?

460
00:40:02,883 --> 00:40:06,375
- No, but I'm not...
- Neither have I. I realized I'm starving.

461
00:40:06,620 --> 00:40:09,180
- We could grab a quick bite.
- Okay.

462
00:40:09,390 --> 00:40:11,255
- Yeah?
- All right.

463
00:40:11,492 --> 00:40:15,121
- Hey, wait up.
- Watch out, man.

464
00:40:15,429 --> 00:40:18,193
- All right.
- Looks pretty good.

465
00:40:18,399 --> 00:40:19,866
- Perfect.
- No, Morgan, it's...

466
00:40:20,067 --> 00:40:21,398
- It's not.
- No, no, trust me.

467
00:40:21,635 --> 00:40:24,103
It's... Okay.

468
00:40:25,573 --> 00:40:26,835
Hi there.

469
00:40:27,041 --> 00:40:29,202
One sec.
Could you hold on for a moment?

470
00:40:29,376 --> 00:40:31,776
- We'd love a table for two.
- The name?

471
00:40:33,647 --> 00:40:35,512
We don't...
